On Kriegsmarine issue tunics a gilt metal pin-backed eagle and swastika emblem was worn over the right breast pocket. No sleeve rings were wrn on this tunic; rank was displayed by means of shoulder straps. All insignia, including buttons, had to be removable to facilitate cleaningMatching white trousers were to be worn with the tunic, along with a whire shirt and black tie. As often as not, white shoes were also worn.$